s      sanam (grant) which permitted them to follow the
Br      hmanical rites. But all the twice-born       whether
Br      hmans, Kshatriyas, or Vaisyas       are entitled to do the
same, and the s      sanam establishes little. The Patn      ls point
out that, in some cases, their g      tras are Br      hmanical. But,
in many instances which could be quoted, Kshatriyas had also
Br      hmanical g      tras.       
It is stated, in the Gazetteer of the Madura district, that the
