century, attached themselves to the Mar      thas in their revolt
against Aurangz      b, and for a long [<a id=
"pb200" href="#pb200" name="pb200">200]time afterwards,
committed raids in all directions, extending their operations to
Southern India. It is on record that        in a raid made upon the
coast extending from Masulipatam northward, the Pind      ris in ten
days plundered 339 villages, burning many, killing and wounding 682
persons, torturing 3,600, and carrying off or destroying property to
the amount of        250,000.       <a class="noteref" id=
"xd21e2914src" href="#xd21e2914" name="xd21e2914src">100 They were
finally suppressed, in Central India, during the Viceroyalty of the
Marquis of Hastings, in 1817.
